# tapps-brain

Persistent cross-session memory system for AI coding assistants. Fully deterministic (no LLM calls), SQLite-backed knowledge store with BM25 ranking, exponential decay, automatic consolidation, cross-project federation, and pluggable vector search.

## Build & Development Commands

```bash
# Install dependencies (uses uv package manager)
uv sync --extra dev

# Install with optional vector search support
uv sync --extra dev --extra vector

# Run all tests (CI-style: exclude benchmarks)
pytest tests/ -v --tb=short -m "not benchmark" --cov=tapps_brain --cov-report=term-missing --cov-fail-under=95

# Production release gate (packaging, version tests, pytest, ruff, mypy, openclaw-plugin)
# Linux / macOS / WSL or Git Bash: bash scripts/release-ready.sh
# OpenClaw doc drift only: python scripts/check_openclaw_docs_consistency.py

# Run a single test file
pytest tests/unit/test_memory_store.py -v

# Lint
ruff check src/ tests/

# Format check
ruff format --check src/ tests/

# Auto-fix lint/format
ruff check --fix src/ tests/
ruff format src/ tests/

# Type check (strict mode)
mypy --strict src/tapps_brain/
```

## Architecture

**Implementation baseline** — `docs/engineering/` (ground-truth architecture, flows, schema, optional paths).

### Source layout: `src/tapps_brain/`

**Storage layer** — `store.py` is the main `MemoryStore` class: in-memory dict + SQLite write-through, thread-safe via `threading.Lock`. `health()` returns `StoreHealthReport` (includes `profile_seed_version` when `profile.seeding.seed_version` is set). `persistence.py` handles SQLite with WAL mode, FTS5 full-text search, and schema migrations (**v1–v17**; v16 = `memory_group`, v17 = `embedding_model_id`; full timeline in `docs/planning/STATUS.md`). MCP tool/resource counts: `docs/generated/mcp-tools-manifest.json`. See `docs/planning/STATUS.md` for a release snapshot.

**Data model** — `models.py` defines `MemoryEntry` (Pydantic v2) with tier-based classification (`MemoryTier`: architectural/pattern/procedural/context), source tracking, scope visibility, and access counting.

**Retrieval** — `retrieval.py` uses composite scoring: relevance 40%, confidence 30%, recency 15%, frequency 15%. `bm25.py` provides Okapi BM25. `fusion.py` implements Reciprocal Rank Fusion for hybrid search. Optional `profile.hybrid_fusion` (`HybridFusionConfig`) tunes per-channel top-k and RRF *k*; used by `inject_memories` → `MemoryRetriever`.

**Memory lifecycle** — `decay.py` applies exponential decay with tier-specific half-lives. `consolidation.py` + `auto_consolidation.py` merge memories deterministically using Jaccard + TF-IDF similarity (no LLM). `gc.py` archives stale memories to `archive.jsonl` (dry-run + metrics, EPIC-044.5). Max-entry eviction: `docs/engineering/data-stores-and-schema.md` (optional `limits.max_entries_per_group`, STORY-044.7). `evaluation.run_consolidation_threshold_sweep` + CLI `maintenance consolidation-threshold-sweep`; merge undo `MemoryStore.undo_consolidation_merge` + CLI `maintenance consolidation-merge-undo` (EPIC-044.4). `MemoryProfile.seeding.seed_version` → `profile_seed_version` on health/stats (EPIC-044.6).

**Safety** — `safety.py` detects prompt injection patterns and sanitizes/blocks RAG content.

**Federation** — `federation.py` enables cross-project memory sharing via hub at `~/.tapps-brain/memory/federated.db`.

### Key design decisions

- **Synchronous by design** — no async/await in core code
- **Write-through cache** — all mutations update both in-memory dict and SQLite
- **Lazy decay** — exponential decay computed on read, not via background tasks
- **Deterministic merging** — consolidation uses similarity thresholds, never LLM calls
- **Max 5,000 entries per project** (default; profile-configurable) — enforced in MemoryStore

## Code Quality

- Python 3.12+, strict mypy, ruff with extensive rule set
- Line length: 100 chars
- Tests ignore ANN (annotations) and PLR (pylint refactor) rules
- Coverage minimum: 95%
- LF line endings enforced via `.gitattributes`

## Cursor (IDE)

- **Quick pointers:** `AGENTS.md` — setup, tests, doc links. **VS Code/Cursor:** `.vscode/settings.json` (Python/Ruff/mypy, 100-char ruler), `.vscode/extensions.json` (recommended extensions), `.vscode/tasks.json` (pytest, ruff, mypy, `release-ready.sh`). **Indexing:** `.cursorignore` excludes `.venv/`, caches, and `openclaw-plugin/node_modules/`.
- **Project MCP config:** `.cursor/mcp.json` wires the same MCP servers as Claude Code where possible:
  - **tapps-mcp** — `tapps-mcp serve --transport` stdio (matches `uv tool install` / `~/.local/bin/tapps-mcp` on PATH).
  - **docs-mcp** — `uv run --directory …/tapps-mcp/packages/docs-mcp docsmcp serve` (same as `claude mcp list`). Uses `${workspaceFolder}/../tapps-mcp/...` so it works when this repo and [tapps-mcp](https://github.com/tapps-mcp/tapps-mcp) are sibling clones (e.g. `~/code/tapps-brain` + `~/code/tapps-mcp`). If your layout differs, edit the `--directory` path to your local `packages/docs-mcp` checkout.
  - **playwright** — `npx @playwright/mcp@latest` (same pattern as Claude / Playwright docs). If Cursor already lists **Plugin MCP → playwright**, remove the `playwright` block from `.cursor/mcp.json` to avoid duplicate browser tools.
- Ensure **PATH** includes `~/.local/bin` (uv tools) and Node/`npx` if you use Playwright via `npx`.
- Optional: add **tapps-brain** memory MCP for dogfooding this repo — see `docs/guides/mcp.md` (`tapps-brain-mcp` + `--project-dir` `${workspaceFolder}`).

